[2026-02-18 07:48:37] [INFO] Product variant images has been updated - Shopidy ID - 10201315672378 - BC id=158 => {"product":{"id":10201315672378,"title":"4-20mA Type Split Core Current Sensor","body_html":"\u003Ch4\u003EMeasure current flowing to equipment\u003C\/h4\u003E\n\u003Cul\u003E\n\u003Cli\u003EMeasures current from 0 to 200A\u003C\/li\u003E\n\u003Cli\u003ESet high or low limit by programming the Sensaphone\u003C\/li\u003E\n\u003Cli\u003ESensaphone will go into alarm when current exceeds limit\u003C\/li\u003E\n\u003Cli\u003EAvailable in 50 Amp or 200 Amp options\u003C\/li\u003E\n\u003C\/ul\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cspan\u003EThe Sensaphone Split Core Current sensor will measure and provide real time current values to any Sensaphone that accepts a 4-20mA signal. When the current level falls outside of the Sensaphone\u2019s programmed high or low limit, the user will receive an alarm which displays or reads the current value. The sensor can be programed to detect current levels from 0 to 200 A. The low profile enclosure allows the sensor to be placed in a single gang electrical box or mounted directly to the wall. The sensors have jumper selectable input ranges, are fast acting and extremely accurate from 1 to 100% of the full scale output, and are factory calibrated using a NIST traceable standard. A 24V DC power supply is required to power the sensor.\u003C\/span\u003E\u003C\/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cspan\u003E\u003C!-- pagebreak --\u003E\u003C\/span\u003E\u003C\/p\u003E\n\u003Ch4\u003E\u003Cspan\u003ETechnical Specifications\u003C\/span\u003E\u003C\/h4\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EMonitored Current Type: \u003C\/strong\u003EAC Current\u003Cstrong\u003E\u003Cbr\u003EMaximum AC Voltage: \u003C\/strong\u003E600 VAC\u003Cstrong\u003E\u003Cspan\u003E\u003Cbr\u003E\u003C\/span\u003E\u003C\/strong\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EIsolation Voltage: \u003C\/strong\u003E\u003Cspan class=\"ProductSpecification-value value-0\"\u003E2200 VAC\u003Cbr\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003ESupply Voltage:\u003C\/strong\u003E \u003Cspan\u003E+8.5 to 30 VDC (Reverse Polarity Protected) | 250 Ohm Load (1-5 VDC): +13.5 to 30 VDC | 500 Ohm Load (2-10 VDC): +18.5 to 30 VDC\u003Cbr\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EMaximum Load Resistance: \u003C\/strong\u003E775 Ohms (Formula: (24 VDC \u2013 8.5 VDC) \/ 0.020A )\u003Cstrong\u003E\u003Cbr\u003ESupply Current: \u003C\/strong\u003E25 mA minimum\u003Cstrong\u003E\u003Cbr\u003EOutput Signal | Maximum Output Signal: \u003C\/strong\u003E4 to 20 mA (2-Wire, Loop Powered) | Limited to 25 mA\u003Cstrong\u003E\u003Cbr\u003EAccuracy: \u003C\/strong\u003E+\/- 1%\u003Cstrong\u003E\u003Cbr\u003EResponse Time: \u003C\/strong\u003E&lt; 600 mS (Rise and Fall Time)\u00a0\u003Cstrong\u003E\u003Cbr\u003E\u003C\/strong\u003E\u003C\/span\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EAperature Size:\u003C\/strong\u003E \u003Cspan\u003E0.75\u201d | 19.05 mm\u003Cbr\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EDIN Rail Mounting: \u003C\/strong\u003E35 mm\u003Cstrong\u003E\u003Cbr\u003EOperating Temperature Range: \u003C\/strong\u003E5\u00b0 to 104\u00baF | -15\u00b0 to 40\u00baC\u003Cstrong\u003E\u003Cbr\u003EOperating Humidity Range: \u003C\/strong\u003E0 to 95%, non-condensing\u003Cstrong\u003E\u003Cbr\u003EStorage Temperature Range: \u003C\/strong\u003E41\u00b0 to 95\u00b0F | 5\u00b0 to 35\u00b0C\u003Cstrong\u003E\u003Cbr\u003EStorage RH Range: \u003C\/strong\u003E40% to 85% RH, non-condensing\u003Cstrong\u003E\u003Cbr\u003EEnclosure Material | Flammability Rating: \u003C\/strong\u003EPC\/ABS (Polycarbonate\/ABS Blend) | UL94-V0\u003Cstrong\u003E\u003Cbr\u003E\u003C\/strong\u003E\u003C\/span\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EWiring Connections:\u003C\/strong\u003E \u003Cspan\u003E2 Position, Screw Terminal Block (Polarity Sensitive)\u003C\/span\u003E\u003Cbr\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EWire Recommendations: \u003C\/strong\u003E2 Conductor (Shielded Cable)\u003Cstrong\u003E\u003Cbr\u003EWire Size: \u003C\/strong\u003E18 to 24 AWG (0.823 mm2 to 0.205 mm2) Copper Wires only\u003Cbr\u003E\u003Cstron