[2026-02-18 07:48:54] [INFO] Product variant images has been updated - Shopidy ID - 10201315868986 - BC id=160 => {"product":{"id":10201315868986,"title":"2.8K Type Ultra Low Temperature Sensor","body_html":"\u003Ch3\u003EMonitor temperatures as low as -85\u00b0C\u003C\/h3\u003E\n\u003Cul\u003E\n\u003Cli style=\"font-weight: 400;\"\u003EMeasures temperature from -121\u00b0 to 115\u00b0F | -85\u00b0 to 80\u00b0C\u003C\/li\u003E\n\u003Cli style=\"font-weight: 400;\"\u003EAccurate to \u00b1 1\u00b0F |\u003Cspan\u003E\u00a0 \u003C\/span\u003E\u00b1 .56\u00b0C\u003C\/li\u003E\n\u003Cli style=\"font-weight: 400;\"\u003EIncludes 12\u2019 of wire and mounting clip\u003C\/li\u003E\n\u003Cli style=\"font-weight: 400;\"\u003ESuitable for use in ultra low freezers\u003C\/li\u003E\n\u003C\/ul\u003E\u003Cp style=\"font-weight: 400;\"\u003EThe Ultra Low Temperature Sensor can be used with most Sensaphone models to measure the temperature in an extremely cold environment. The Sensaphone will trigger an alarm when the temperature falls outside of the programmed high or low temperature limit. The sensor\u2019s coated wire prevents cracking and allows it to be placed inside of freezers that go as low as -85\u00b0C. The sensor is ideal for medical or research cold storage freezers that keep a constant temperature below the limits of other Sensaphone temperature sensors. The included 12 feet of coated wire can be extended with optional accessory wire.\u003C\/p\u003E\n\u003Cp style=\"font-weight: 400;\"\u003EAn optional NIST traceable certificate is available.\u003C\/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cspan\u003E\u003C!-- pagebreak --\u003E\u003C\/span\u003E\u003C\/p\u003E\n\u003Ch4\u003E\u003Cspan\u003ETechnical Specifications\u003C\/span\u003E\u003C\/h4\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cspan\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003ESensor Temperature Range:\u003C\/strong\u003E -121\u00b0 to 176\u00b0F | -85\u00b0 to 80\u00b0C\u003Cbr\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EAccuracy\u003C\/strong\u003E: 1\u00b0F | .56\u00b0C\u00a0\u003C