[2026-02-18 07:53:21] [INFO] Product variant images has been updated - Shopidy ID - 10201318785338 - BC id=209 => {"product":{"id":10201318785338,"title":"WSG Wireless Temperature Sensor in Buffered Bottle","body_html":"\u003Ch3\u003EBuffer momentary temperature fluctuations\u003C\/h3\u003E\n\u003Cul\u003E\n\u003Cli\u003EMeasures temperature from -20\u00b0 to 115\u00b0F | -28\u00b0 to 46\u00b0C\u003C\/li\u003E\n\u003Cli\u003EAccurate to \u00b1 1\u00b0F |\u00a0 \u00b1 .56\u00b0C\u003C\/li\u003E\n\u003Cli\u003EChoose between a bottle filled with glass beads or glycol\u003C\/li\u003E\n\u003Cli\u003ECommunicates wirelessly with WSG30 base unit up to 300\u2019 away\u003C\/li\u003E\n\u003Cli\u003EIncludes two AA batteries\u003C\/li\u003E\n\u003Cli\u003EOptional power supply available\u003C\/li\u003E\n\u003C\/ul\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cspan\u003EThe Wireless Temperature Sensors are used exclusively with the WSG30 \u003C\/span\u003Esystem to measure the temperature of objects in a refrigerator or freezer\u003Cspan\u003E. By placing the sensor in a bottle filled with glass beads or glycol users will receive a reading that represents the temperature of the contents of inside of the refrigerator rather than the ambient air temperature. When the temperature falls outside of the WSG30 system\u2019s programmed high or low limit, the user will receive an alarm via text message or email. The external probe is wired to the sensor with the included 12\u2019 of wire. The sensor includes two AA alkaline batteries which will power the sensor for up to two years. An optional plug-in power supply is also available, in which case the batteries then become a backup if the main AC power fails. The wireless sensor can be placed up to 300\u2019 away from the WSG30 or further if multiple sensors are used to create a mesh network.\u003C\/span\u003E\u003C\/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cspan\u003E\u003C!-- pagebreak --\u003E\u003C\/span\u003E\u003C\/p\u003E\n\u003Ch4\u003E\u003Cspan\u003ETechnical S