[2026-02-18 07:55:44] [INFO] Product variant images has been updated - Shopidy ID - 10201320456506 - BC id=243 => {"product":{"id":10201320456506,"title":"IMS Solution Ultra Low Temperature Sensor","body_html":"\u003Ch3 style=\"font-weight: 400;\"\u003EMonitor temperatures as low as -85\u00b0C\u003C\/h3\u003E\n\u003Cul\u003E\n\u003Cli style=\"font-weight: 400;\"\u003EOptional glass bead vial will buffer any momentary fluctuations that may cause a preliminary alarm dial out, such as defrost cycles, opening of doors, and fans circulating air\u003C\/li\u003E\n\u003Cli style=\"font-weight: 400;\"\u003EMeasures temperatures from -121\u00b0 to 53\u00b0F | -86\u00b0 to 12\u00b0C\u003C\/li\u003E\n\u003Cli style=\"font-weight: 400;\"\u003EAvailable with NIST certification\u003C\/li\u003E\n\u003C\/ul\u003E\u003Cp style=\"font-weight: 400;\"\u003EThe Ultra Low Temperature Sensors are designed to connect to the Sensaphone IMS product line and monitor temperatures in refrigerators or freezers. The electrical connection between the sensor and IMS unit is made via the attached RJ-45 patch cable. The sensor probe may be secured inside equipment using the included clamp or it may be hung using tie wraps. Do not install the black plastic enclosure inside of a refrigerator or freezer. This sensor includes a remote temperature probe so that temperature measurements can be made in a freezer or other harsh environments. The sensor is available with an optional glass bead vial which helps to prevent false temperature readings when a refrigerator or freezer door is opened or goes into a defrost cycle. In addition they are available with an optional NIST temperature certification.\u003C\/p\u003E\n\u003Cp style=\"font-weight: 400;\"\u003E\u003Cbr\u003EThe Ultra Low Temperature Sensors come with a 7\u2032 cable with an RJ-45 plug on the end and a weatherproof probe with 12\u2032 of cable. If the sensor installation is close to the IMS unit, you can plug it directly into an IMS environmental input. If the cable is too short you can use the included RJ-45 adaptor and a longer patch cable to extend the length. For applications where the sensor may be far from the IMS unit, you may utilize your existing network wiring infrastructure. For example, the sensor may be installed in another room or another floor. Connect the sensor to your structured wiring network via an RJ-45 jack. At the other end, connect a patch cable from your structured wiring patch panel directly to the Host or Node environment input.\u00a0\u003C\/p\u003E\n\u003Ch3 style=\"font-weight: 400;\"\u003E\u003C!-- pagebreak --\u003E\u003C\/h3\u003E\n\u003Ch3 style=\"font-weight: 400;\"\u003ETechnical Specifications\u003C\/h3\u003E\n\u003Cp style=\"font-weight: 400;\"\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003ESensor Temperature Range:\u003C\/strong\u003E\u00a0-122\u00b0 to 53\u00b0F | -86\u00b0 to 12\u00b0C\u003Cbr\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EAccuracy:\u003C\/strong\u003E\u00a03\u00b0F | 1.7\u00b0C \u00a0\u003Cbr\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EConnection:\u003C\/strong\u003E\u00a0RJ45\u003Cbr\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EHousing:\u003C\/strong\u003E\u00a0Plastic\u003Cbr\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EDimensions:\u003C\/strong\u003E\u00a02.1 x 1.3 x .6\" | 53 x 33 x 15mm\u003Cbr\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003ESensor Series:\u003C\/strong\u003E\u00a0IMS Solution\u003Cbr\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003ENotes\u003C\/strong\u003E:\u00a0Available with NIST Certification\u003C\/p\u003E\n\u003Ch3\u003EDownloads\u003C\/h3\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\u003Ca href=\"https:\/\/cdn.shopify.com\/s\/files\/1\/0987\/4738\/4122\/files\/CS_IMS-4814E.pdf\"\u003EIMS Solution Ultra Low Temperature Sensor\u003C\/a\u003E\u003Cbr\u003E\u003Ca href=\"https:\/\/cdn.shopify.com\/s\/files\/1\/0987\/4738\/4122\/files\/CS_IMS-4815E.pdf\"\u003EIMS Solution Ultra Low Temperature Sensor in Glass Bead Vial\u003C\/a\u003E\u003C\/p\u003E","vendor":"Sensaphone","product_type":"physical","created_at":"2026-02-18T01:55:43-05:00","handle":"ims-solution-ultra-low-temperature-sensor","updated_at":"2026-02-1